The following query searches for customer accounts between
`250000` and `300000`. It includes a [$limit](manual/reference/operator/aggregation/limit)
stage to limit the output to `5` results and a
[$project](manual/reference/operator/aggregation/project) stage to exclude all fields except
`accounts` and `name`.

**Input:**

```javascript
db.customers.aggregate([
  {
    "$search": {
      "range": {
        "path": "accounts",
        "gt": 250000,
        "lt": 400000
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "$limit": 5
  },
  {
    "$project": {
      "_id": 0,
      "accounts": 1,
      "name": 1
    }
  }
])
```

